3P7.F.summary: Pandora A/S designs, manufactures, and markets hand-finished and contemporary jewelry worldwide. The company offers jewelry, including silver and gold, man-made stones, gemstones, cultured pearls, and diamonds, as well as enamel, glass, leather, and textile products. Its products primarily include charms, bracelets, rings, earrings, necklaces, and pendants. The company operates through a network of 2,770 concept stores, which include 1,397 company owned stores; and 4,657 other points of sale, as well as eSTOREs. Pandora A/S was founded in 1982 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark.

AAB.CO.summary: Aalborg Boldspilklub A/S operates a professional football stadium in Denmark. The company offers tickets to football games and merchandise to private individuals and corporate customers. Aalborg Boldspilklub A/S was founded in 1885 and is based in Aalborg, Denmark.

AGF-B.CO.summary: AGF A/S operates sports and event activities in Denmark. It operates through two segments, Football and Facilities. The Football segment offers football matches shown on TV, sponsorships, transfers of football players, football matches, and physiotherapy. The Facilities segment rents properties and premises, sales in connection with events, conferences, and concerts. It also operates restaurants that provide catering for events. The company was formerly known as Aarhus Elite A/S and changed its name to AGF A/S in December 2017. AGF A/S was founded in 1880 and is based in Aarhus, Denmark.

ASGRF.summary: Astralis Group A/S operates as an esports company. It owns three esports teams under the Astralis, Origen, and Future FC brands. The company was founded in 2016 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

GABR.CO.summary: Gabriel Holding A/S develops, manufactures, and sells upholstery fabrics, components, upholstered surfaces, and related products and services. It operates through two segments, Fabrics and Letting of Office Facilities. The Fabrics segment offers concern furniture fabrics and related textile products to manufacturers and users in upholstered furniture, seats, and upholstered surfaces. The Letting of Office Facilities segment lets office premises in Aalborg. It operates in Denmark, Germany, the United States, Mexico, Asia, and Other European countries. Gabriel Holding A/S was founded in 1851 and is based in Aalborg, Denmark.

HAPPY.CO.summary: Happy Helper A/S operates an online booking platform for cleaning in Denmark. Its platform allows to book cleaning services for private homes, as well as final cleaning on relocations, smaller offices, or stairs. The company is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

PARKEN.CO.summary: PARKEN Sport & Entertainment A/S operates in the sports industry in Denmark. The company operates a football stadium and club, and office properties. It is also involved in the operation of Lalandia holiday and activity centers; and the rental and sale of holiday homes. The company was founded in 1991 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

SBS.CO.summary: Scandinavian Brake Systems A/S, together with its subsidiaries, provides automotive and friction parts for the automotive aftermarket in Europe and internationally. The company's SBS Automotive segments sources, completes, and distributes brake and wear parts, including mechanical and hydraulic brake parts; steering parts and wheel bearing kits; suspension and transmission parts; clutch parts; and starters and alternators primarily under the NK brand or as private labels. It also operates sales and distribution platforms. In addition, this segment distributes its products directly to distributors, including international groups, capital chains, purchasing groups, and independent distributors. Its SBS Friction segments develops, manufactures, and sells brake parts and friction technology for motorcycles, scooters, and other ATV/UTV vehicles, as well as for various specialized areas that apply friction technology, including wind turbines. This segment primarily offers brake pads, brake discs, brake shoes, and accessory parts. The company was formerly known as OBTEC and changed its name to Scandinavian Brake Systems A/S in 2003. Scandinavian Brake Systems A/S was founded in 1964 and is based in Svendborg, Denmark. Scandinavian Brake Systems A/S is a subsidiary of Stiholt Holding A/S.

SIF.CO.summary: Silkeborg IF Invest A/S operates a professional football club in Denmark. It also engages in the rental and operation of business area; and hotel and conference activities. The company was formerly known as SIF Football Support A/S and changed its name to Silkeborg IF Invest A/S in 2008. Silkeborg IF Invest A/S was founded in 1917 and is based in Silkeborg, Denmark.

TIV.CO.summary: Tivoli A/S engages in entertainment and recreational activities. The company operates and maintains gardens. The company offers rides, games, shows, events, and concerts. It also operates restaurants, as well as online casino through Danske Spi. Tivoli A/S was founded in 1843 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.
